: The 
<typeStatus id="54E8BDD3FF94FFE9FE3EFA3CDACFDAB0" box="[436,486,1454,1477]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FD9FFA3DDBF3DA96" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1913" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nivicola">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FD9FFA3DDBF3DA96" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sylvilagus nivicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a specimen collected at 
<quantity id="4CABAE94FF94FFE9FDA5FA5ED9A4DA96" box="[559,653,1484,1507]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="4800.0">
<elevation id="007EE442FF94FFE9FDA5FA5ED9A4DA96" box="[559,653,1484,1507]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="4800.0">4800 m</elevation>
</quantity>
‘‘en el límite de nieves perpetuas’’ on 
<location id="8E8C55AAFF94FFE9FDC0FA7BDBCFD968" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FAB267FF94FFE9FF37FACCD9D2DC56:8E8C55AAFF94FFE9FDC0FA7BDBCFD968" county="Antisana" municipality="Ten" name="Cerro Antisana" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Cerro Antisana</location>
, about 
<quantity id="4CABAE94FF94FFE9FECCF994DABFD968" box="[326,406,1542,1565]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
south of 
<location id="8E8C55AAFF94FFE9FD9CF994D9A4D968" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FAB267FF94FFE9FF37FACCD9D2DC56:8E8C55AAFF94FFE9FD9CF994D9A4D968" box="[534,653,1542,1565]" county="Antisana" municipality="Ten" name="Papallacta" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Papallacta</location>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FF0EF9B6DA67D94E" author="Cabrera, A." box="[132,334,1572,1595]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref21563" refString="Cabrera, A. 1913. Dos mamiferos nuevos de la fauna neotropical. Trabajos del Museo de Ciencias Naturales (Serie Zoologica) 9: 1 - 16, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1913">Cabrera, 1913: 6</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B88990BFF94FFE9FEEFF9B6DAB9D94E" box="[357,400,1572,1595]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Ten</collectingMunicipality>
<typeStatus id="54E8BDD3FF94FFE9FE12F9B6D9A4D94E" box="[408,653,1572,1595]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">additional specimens</typeStatus>
of rabbits from 
<collectingCounty id="628D7BFDFF94FFE9FEC1F9D3DA9BD92D" box="[331,434,1601,1624]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Antisana</collectingCounty>
(
<specimenCode id="DBF5AB0AFF94FFE9FE40F9D3DBEFD900" collectionCode="AMNH" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">AMNH 66659– 66668</specimenCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
were subsequently collected between 4115 and 
<quantity id="4CABAE94FF94FFE9FF79F9EEDA67D9E6" box="[243,334,1660,1683]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.265" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="4265.0">4265 m</quantity>
by H.E. Anthony in 1923. Other material from Antisana (in the BMNH) was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FED8F924DAD5D9B8" author="Laurie, E. M." box="[338,508,1718,1741]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="268 - 276" refId="ref23507" refString="Laurie, E. M. 1955. Notes on some mammals from Ecuador. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 34 (128): 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1955">Laurie (1955)</bibRefCitation>
, and a few more specimens are scattered among other museums (e.g., MCN, MNCN).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC0371FF94FFE9FD53FF6ED823DDD8" blockId="34.[700,1229,193,803]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
TAXONOMY: All of the material at hand is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FCD5FE8BDF47DE45" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[863,1134,281,304]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FCD5FE8BDF47DE45" box="[863,1134,281,304]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sylvilagus brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the sense of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FCA4FEA4DF33DE38" author="Hershkovitz, P." box="[814,1050,310,333]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="327 - 375" refId="ref22909" refString="Hershkovitz, P. 1950. Mammals of northern Colombia preliminary report no. 6: rabbits (Leporidae), with notes on the classification and distribution of the South American forms. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 100: 327 - 375." type="journal article" year="1950">Hershkovitz (1950)</bibRefCitation>
, the last comprehensive taxonomic review of South American lagomorph taxonomy. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FBB5FEE3D820DED0" author="Hershkovitz, P." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="327 - 375" refId="ref22909" refString="Hershkovitz, P. 1950. Mammals of northern Colombia preliminary report no. 6: rabbits (Leporidae), with notes on the classification and distribution of the South American forms. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 100: 327 - 375." type="journal article" year="1950">Hershkovitz (1950)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FCFBFE1DDFB9DED0" authority="Cabrera (1913)" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1913" box="[881,1168,398,422]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nivicola">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FCFBFE1DD8E6DED3" box="[881,975,399,422]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">nivicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FC51FE1CDFB9DED0" author="Cabrera, A." box="[987,1168,398,421]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref21563" refString="Cabrera, A. 1913. Dos mamiferos nuevos de la fauna neotropical. Trabajos del Museo de Ciencias Naturales (Serie Zoologica) 9: 1 - 16, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1913">Cabrera (1913)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FC28FE3EDF6FDEB6" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[930,1094,428,451]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FC28FE3EDF6FDEB6" box="[930,1094,428,451]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FB0BFE3ED820DE95" author="Laurie, E. M." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="268 - 276" refId="ref23507" refString="Laurie, E. M. 1955. Notes on some mammals from Ecuador. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 34 (128): 268 - 276." type="journal article" year="1955">Laurie (1955)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FC31FE5BDF30DE95" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1913" box="[955,1049,457,480]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nivicola">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FC31FE5BDF30DE95" box="[955,1049,457,480]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">nivicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FBE9FE5BD9D2DE8B" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. b. andinus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FC99FE74D8FFDE88" author="Thomas, O." box="[787,982,486,509]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="544 - 553" refId="ref25092" refString="Thomas, O. 1897 b. Descriptions of new bats and rodents from America. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 6 (20): 544 - 553." type="journal article" year="1897">Thomas, 1897b</bibRefCitation>
). The current treatment (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC27E80FF94FFE9FC80FD96D8F8DD6E" author="Hoffmann, R. S." box="[778,977,516,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="807 - 827" refId="ref23095" refString="Hoffmann, R. S. 1993. Oder Lagomorpha. In D. E. Wilson and D. M. Reeder (editors), Mammal species of the world, 2 nd ed.: 807 - 827. Washington, DC: Smithsonian Institution Press." type="book chapter" year="1993">Hoffmann, 1993</bibRefCitation>
) of 41 nominal taxa ranging from southern 
<collectingCountry id="F34443E1FF94FFE9FC54FDB3DF1EDD4D" box="[990,1079,545,568]" name="Mexico" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F34443E1FF94FFE9FD36FDACD819DD20" box="[700,816,574,597]" name="Argentina" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Argentina</collectingCountry>
as synonyms or subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5378F2FF94FFE9FB3DFDADD86BDD06" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B927DF63FF94FFE9FB3DFDADD86BDD06" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
obviously merits critical scrutiny, but is far beyond the scope of this faunal report.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34950FAFF94FFE9FD53FD26D9D2DC56" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEC0371FF94FFE9FD53FD26D9D2DC56" blockId="34.[700,1229,193,803]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">REMARKS: Although I did not collect any rabbits near Papallacta, they were abundant in grassy habitats throughout the páramo zone.</paragraph>
